# MindVault CODEOWNERS
#
# Maps repository paths to required reviewers so GitHub automatically
# requests review from the right owner(s) on every pull request.
# Patterns are matched top-to-bottom; the last matching rule wins.
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default owner for anything not covered by a more specific rule below.
* @archanavdev

# Smart-contract workspace — any change here must be reviewed carefully
# because the contract is deployed on-chain and upgrades are permanent.
/contract/ @archanavdev

# Server — core API, DB schema, migrations, and business logic.
/server/ @archanavdev

# Web frontend
/web/ @archanavdev

# Model Context Protocol server
/mcp/ @archanavdev

# Shared packages (generated Soroban bindings, registry-client).
# Binding drift in packages/ breaks server/, web/, and mcp/ simultaneously.
/packages/ @archanavdev

# GitHub configuration — workflows, branch-protection rules, issue templates.
# Changes here affect the whole team's process, so require an extra review.
/.github/ @archanavdev
